          }
        ],
        "name": "Coda",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 191,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Treasure Vault pg. 217",
              "aonid": 191,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Treasure Vault pg. 217",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Treasure Vault",
            "page": 217,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Instruments with the coda trait work mostly like staves and have the staff trait. There are two differences: Coda instruments are in the form of musical instruments, and they can be prepared only by bards. Because they're not physically staves, you can't attack with a coda instrument, nor can you etch it with weapon runes.  \n  \n The process of preparing a coda instrument involves playing significant portions of songs related to the spells within the instrument\u2014either old standards or ones of your own creation. This leaves magical reverberations within the instrument that allow you to complete the songs by playing their coda later in the day.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 151,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f6cdd9b53ed4b4a360df284df4503b27",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Staff",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 278",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 278",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 278,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This magic item holds spells of a particular theme and allows a spellcaster to cast additional spells by preparing the staff.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
